dct_description_sm: Prepared by the Army Map Service (GE), Corps of Engineers, U.S. Army, Washington, D.C. , original map compiled by U.S. Geological Survey. Variant title: Indiana 1:25,000. Filing title: Columbia City, Indiana : Whitley County. Standard map series designation: Series V851 Sheet 3966 III NW. Edition 1--AMS 1. Transverse Mercator projection. Series , V851. Relief shown by contours and spot heights. Shows roads, railroads, boundaries, buildings, mines, and natural features. Marginal maps: Index to boundaries -- Index to adjoining sheets. Contour interval 10 feet. "Copied in 1957 from Indiana, 1:24,000, USGS, Columbia City, 1955. Original map compiled by U.S. Geological Survey. Culture and drainage in part compiled from aerial photographs taken 1948. Topography by planetable methods, 1955. Horizontal and vertical control by USGS and USC&GS. ... Scale changed, Universal Transverse Mercator Grid added, and marginal data revised 1958." "First printing, 11-59." "Printed by Army Map Service, Corps of Engineers, 11-59." Printed with vegetation.
Imprint: Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, Corps of Engineers, Department of the Army, 1959.
Dimensions: 56 x 45 cm or smaller; Scale: 1:25,000
dct_creator_sm: United States. Army Map Service; Geological Survey (U.S.)
